notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Extract Mahidol AQI HTML
components.description: Scrapes the Mahidol University AQI webpage and saves the raw HTML to a local file.

components.name: Transform Mahidol AQI to JSON
components.description: Parses the saved HTML, extracts AQI metrics, validates freshness against the database, and writes a structured JSON file.

connections.purpose: Check for duplicate records and validate freshness

components.name: Load Mahidol AQI into PostgreSQL
components.description: Inserts the parsed AQI JSON into dimension and fact tables in PostgreSQL, handling conflicts and ensuring transactional integrity.

components.name: Notify PM2.5 Email Alert
components.description: Sends email alerts via SMTP when AQI values exceed defined thresholds; skips execution if AQI is within safe range.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful load; may be skipped based on AQI thresholds.

connections.purpose: Send alert emails via Gmail SMTP

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

http_timeout_seconds.description: Timeout for the HTTP request to the Mahidol AQI website

encoding.description: Character encoding used when writing the HTML file

datetime_format.description: Datetime format string used to parse timestamps from the HTML source

conflict_strategy.description: Strategy for handling primarykey conflicts when inserting into dimension tables

aqi_thresholds.description: AQI threshold levels that trigger email alerts (safe: 050, moderate: 51100, unhealthy: 101200, hazardous: >200)

email_config_path.description: Path to the configuration file containing SMTP credentials

recipients_file.description: File containing the list of email recipients for PM2.5 alerts

POSTGRES_CONN.description: Connection identifier for the PostgreSQL data warehouse

SMTP_SERVER.description: SMTP server hostname used for sending email alerts

SMTP_PORT.description: Port number for the SMTP server

EMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH.description: Filesystem path to the file containing SMTP authentication credentials

RECIPIENTS_FILE.description: Filesystem path to the file listing email recipients for PM2.5 alerts

produces: Email notifications to PM2.5 alert recipients

sources: Mahidol University AQI website (HTML page scraped from https://mahidol.ac.th/aqireport/)
sinks: PostgreSQL data warehouse tables (dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factmahidolaqitable)
Email alerts sent via Gmail SMTP to configured recipients
